---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | hospitalbillnegotiationcalc.com';
const description = 'Privacy policy for hospitalbillnegotiationcalc.com — what data we collect, how we use it, and how to opt out of advertising cookies.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective date:</strong> January 1, 2026</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>hospitalbillnegotiationcalc.com is committed to protecting user privacy. This policy describes what data is collected when you use this site, how it is used, and your options for limiting data collection. We do not collect personal information directly and do not sell reader data to third parties.</p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We do not require account creation, registration, or any submission of personal information to use this site. The calculator processes all inputs locally in your browser — no bill amount, income, or insurance status information is transmitted to our servers or to any third party.</p>
  <p>We do use two third-party services that collect aggregate usage data: Google AdSense (advertising) and Google Analytics (traffic analysis). Both services are described below.</p>

  <h2>Google AdSense</h2>
  <p>This site displays advertising through Google AdSense (publisher ID: ca-pub-6434377544325972). Google AdSense uses cookies and similar tracking technologies to serve relevant advertisements based on your browsing history and interests. Google may collect information about your visits to this and other websites to provide interest-based advertising.</p>
  <p>You can opt out of personalized advertising through <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ad Settings</a> or through the <a href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Network Advertising Initiative opt-out tool</a>. You can also manage cookie preferences through your browser settings. Note that opting out of personalized ads does not remove advertising from the site — it means you will see non-personalized ads instead.</p>
  <p>Google's use of advertising cookies is governed by <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

  <h2>Google Analytics</h2>
  <p>We use Google Analytics to understand aggregate traffic patterns — how many visitors the site receives, which pages are most visited, and general geographic distribution of visitors. Google Analytics collects data in aggregate and does not identify individual users. We do not use Analytics data to identify, profile, or track individual visitors.</p>
  <p>Google Analytics data is subject to <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>. You can opt out of Google Analytics tracking using the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.</p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>This site uses cookies placed by Google AdSense and Google Analytics. We do not place first-party cookies beyond what is necessary for basic site functionality. You can manage cookie settings in your browser, but disabling all cookies may affect ad display and site functionality.</p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>This site is not directed at children under the age of 13 and does not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has submitted personal information, contact us at <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this privacy policy to reflect changes in our data practices or applicable law. Material changes will be noted with an updated effective date. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about this privacy policy? Email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
